            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "While there are plenty of detractors for the Porsche 928 today, back in the late 70s the car almost became the successor of the 911. It was a hot performance vehicle for the day, boasting a beefy 4.5-liter V8 pushed back far enough to make for balanced handling for a front-engine car.",
